    "The central component of the improved ML algorithm is the geometric inductive bias built into our feature mapping x 2 ½À1,1 m 7!ϕðxÞ 2 R m ϕ.",
    "To describe the ML algorithm, we first need to present some definitions relating to this geometric structure.",
    "We consider n qubits arranged at locations, or sites, in a d-dimensional space, e.g., a spin chain (d = 1), a square lattice (d = 2), or a cubic lattice (d = 3).",
    "This geometry is characterized by the distance d qubit ði,i 0 Þ between any two qubits i and i 0.",
    "Using the distance d qubit between qubits, we can define the geometry of local observables."
